    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/commit/5012dcbdaefa7a11a8dfcd9ff264655e9860ee50"/>
    <title>
        Fix iframe resize handler when re-attached to DOM (#3527)
    </title>
    <updated>2016-10-31T07:47:28Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/3874900?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>simonbrunel</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/simonbrunel</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Fix iframe resize handler when re-attached to DOM (#3527)

When the iframe is attached to the DOM, its content is reloaded (invaliding the resize listener) so make sure to install the handler after the iframe is loaded. Optimize resize events by throttling resize process until the next animation frame. Rewrite the unit test &amp;quot;waitForResize&amp;quot; method, the previous one (timeout) was too weak and most tests was failing on FF.&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
